**MAIN DB**

This database was created with the objective of saving all the information that may be generated from bank users who make purchases or from a STORE with which **PLINK has made an agreement to create user LOYALTY programs.**

**STORE information such as:**

* Specific store info  
* Store of the business to which it belongs  
* Relationship between the store ID and the entity ID (which we find in TX\_DB), payment methods  
* Payment method from the store to Plink  
* Store username and password to enter the Merchant APP  
* Campaigns created for the store  
* User actions towards store campaigns  
* Others

**USER information such as:**

* User account\_id from the bank  
* ID of the bank to which the user belongs (Parent)  
* Exact FIID to which the user belongs (Branch)  
* ID assigned to the bank user in our database  
* Actions performed by the user to stores with campaigns  
* Consumer credit card details  
* Analysis of user purchases by commercial district  
* Others

* The **ID** which is the place that the record has in the table

# **Consumer\_business\_entity\_priority\_score**

***Objective:** This table aims to record the relevance that a store has for a consumer, as well as how relevant a user is in terms of their amount of purchases for the CD of that Entity and for their FIID.*

* The **CONSUMER\_ID** which represents the ID that this user has in the [Consumer](#heading=h.cdkv9wxenkrb) table  
* The **BUSINESS\_ENTITY\_ID**Which is the business with which we are doing the relevance study  
* The **PERCENT CONSUMER CD SPEND FROM CONSUMER TOTAL LAST 180 DAYS** in which we will obtain the percentage of purchases that the consumer made in the last 180 days in the Commercial District to which the Business\_entity\_id belongs of the total of their purchases in the same period  
* The **PERCENT CONSUMER BE SPEND FROM CONSUMER CD TOTAL LAST 180 DAYS** in which we will obtain the percentage of purchases that the consumer made in the last 180 days in the Business\_entity\_id of the total purchases made in the Commercial District in the same period  
* The **PERCENT BE SPEND FROM CD FI TOTAL LAST 180 DAYS** in which we will obtain the percentage of purchases that the consumer made in the last 180 days in the Business\_entity\_id of the total of their purchases made in the same period

# **Consumer\_store\_score**

***Objective:** This table aims to store a relationship between a consumer and the stores that are relevant to him, along with the source of their relationship (Top verified local stores, Opted in stores, Engaged stores, Relevant CD stores, Relevant CD neighbor stores, Featured stores) and the score of how important the store is to the user.*

* The **CONSUMER\_ID** which is the consumer ID to which some stores will be associated  
* The **STORE\_ID** It is the ID of the store with which the consumer is being associated.  
* The **SOURCE** It is the group assigned to the store with respect to the relationship that the consumer has with the store.  
* The **SCORE** It is the result of a calculation that defines the relevance of a store for the consumer *(this data is taken from the **normalized\_score** field of the **consumer\_business\_entity\_priority\_score** table)*

# **Transactions**

***Objective:** Esta tabla tiene como objetivo guardar los datos de las trasacciones hechas por un consumidor a las STORES y la fuente de donde sabemos que se hicieron estas transacciones*

* The **CONSUMER\_ID** is the ID of the consumer who made the purchase  
* The **STORE\_ID** is the ID of the store where the user purchased, a store that is registered with Plink  
* The **SOURCE\_ID** is the company that provided us with the transaction  
* **The TIMESTAMP** is the date on which the operation was performed

# **Feature\_flags**

***Objective:** This table is related to having all feature flags of the system, using this table we can deactivate or activate any released feature that contains in the table.*

* The **NAME** is where we store the name of the future flag, using the pattern of the ***SCREAMING\_SNAKE\_CASE*** for the names of the feature flag.  
* The **ENABLED** is a boolean (true of false) field where we can store if the feature flag is enabled or disabled.
